To create a proxy in ASP.NET Core, you can use the `HttpClient` class to make a request to the target endpoint and then return the response from the target endpoint. Here's an example of how you can do this:

**Using HttpClient**

```csharp
[ApiController]
[Route("[controller]")]
public class ProxyController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly IHttpClientFactory _httpClientFactory;

    public ProxyController(IHttpClientFactory httpClientFactory)
    {
        _httpClientFactory = httpClientFactory;
    }

    [HttpGet("{url}")]
    public async Task<IActionResult> GetAsync(string url)
    {
        var client = _httpClientFactory.CreateClient();
        var request = new HttpRequestMessage(HttpMethod.Get, url);
        var response = await client.SendAsync(request);

        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        var responseBody = await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync();
        return Ok(responseBody);
    }
}
```

